# Hub Session Start

Before creating tickets or making code edits, confirm the active Hub client, project, and team member for this workspace.

## Every new agent chat (required)

Run this checklist on the **first message** of every new Cursor agent conversation — even if `.hub-session.json` already exists.

1. Run `node tools/hub-workflow-cli.mjs whoami` — show the authenticated team member and token name.
2. Run `node tools/hub-workflow-cli.mjs show-session`.
3. **Ask the user to confirm** via AskQuestion:
   - If session exists: "Continue as {client_name} / {project_name} / {team_member_name}?"
   - If no session or user wants to change: proceed with full selection below.
4. If session is missing or user declines the existing session:
   - Run `node tools/hub-workflow-cli.mjs list-clients`
   - **Ask the user which client** this work is for
   - Run `node tools/hub-workflow-cli.mjs list-projects --client-id "<client-uuid>"`
   - **Ask the user which project** under that client
   - **Confirm team member** matches `whoami` output — the session team member must be the token owner
   - If user says they are a different person, **stop** and tell them to update `APPDOERS_CURSOR_TOKEN` in `.env.local` or `.env.hub`
   - Run `node tools/hub-workflow-cli.mjs set-session --client-id "<uuid>" --project-id "<uuid>" --team-user-id "<uuid>" --team-member-name "<name>"`
5. Confirm with `show-session` before `create-ticket`.
6. Echo confirmed `client_name`, `project_name`, `team_member_name`, and ids in the first status update.

## Rules

- Never guess client, project, or team member — always ask when session is missing or unconfirmed
- Match folder context only as a hint; user confirmation wins
- Multiple clients can share the same project name — always use ids from `list-projects --client-id`
- `create-ticket` uses the session project when `--project-id` is omitted
- `claim-ticket` uses session team member for assignment when `--assigned-to` is omitted
- To switch client/project mid-session: `clear-session` then repeat the checklist

## Portable setup (any repo)

Install from `hub-cursor-kit/` in Appdoers CRM:

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File "path\to\hub-cursor-kit\install.ps1" -TargetProject "C:\path\to\your-project"
```

Requires `tools/hub-workflow-cli.mjs`, `tools/hub-ticket-time.mjs`, `.cursor/rules/` Hub rule files, and `.env.local` (or parent `.env.hub`) with `APPDOERS_HUB_URL` and `APPDOERS_CURSOR_TOKEN`.
